def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test the hypotheses by generating images with variations on the common elements found
    original_prompt = "a mosque silhouette against a clear sky"
    edit_prompts = [
        "replace the mosque with a modern skyscraper",
        "replace the clear sky with a cloudy sky",
        "replace the mosque with a gothic cathedral",
        "keep the mosque but change the time to broad daylight"
    ]
    
    # Generate the original images and then apply the edits
    all_images, all_prompts = tools.edit_images([original_prompt] * len(edit_prompts), edit_prompts)
    
    # Get neuron activations for all the images
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(all_images)
    
    # Describe the images for a better understanding of the content
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, all_prompts)
    
    # Document the experiment
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, all_prompts, descriptions)
```

def execute_command(system, tools):
    # Test further by trying different shapes and times of day
    prompts = [
        "a silhouette of a mosque with minarets during sunset",
        "a silhouette of a mosque without minarets during sunset",
        "a silhouette of a skyscraper during sunset",
        "the interior of a mosque with decorative Islamic patterns",
        "a minaret against the night sky",
        "a dome structure with no religious context against the sky"
    ]
    
    # Generate images for the new prompts
    images = tools.text2image(prompts)
    
    # Get neuron activations for all the new images
    activation_list, activation_map_list = system.call_neuron(images)
    
    # Describe the images for a better understanding of their content
    descriptions = tools.describe_images(activation_map_list, prompts)
    
    # Document the experiment
    tools.save_experiment_log(activation_list, activation_map_list, prompts, descriptions)
```
